NavBar Cover Art by developer

As written in Youtube Terms of Service,

"You shall not download any Content unless you see a “download” or similar link displayed by YouTube on the Service for that Content.You shall not copy, reproduce, make available online or electronically transmit, publish, adapt, distribute, transmit, broadcast, display, sell, license, or otherwise exploit any Content for any other purposes without the prior written consent of YouTube or the respective licensors of the Content. YouTube and its licensors reserve all rights not expressly granted in and to the Service and the Content." [Source: https://www.youtube.com/static?template=terms ( goto section 5B)].

So, You are violating Youtube TOS while downloading and saving media content from youtube offline. The developer isn't intended to do that and doesn't support that, and takes NO responsibility for what you do using YouP3.

WYSN : Basic Mode uses WebView API(s), and it uses a normal API which is written to work in this way. It may be unstable, can\'t bypass ads, provides only AUDIO files (mp3) but normally doesn\'t fail anyway.

WYSN : Advanced Mode uses a library which also depends on a library which depends on - How Google writes YouTube\'s \'JavaScript(s)\'. So, though it provides options to download much type of video/audio(s) it can fail. Also, it\'s written by third-party, so support also can be stopped from them.
